\fB\fI{mime_types, [{MimeType, Extension}] | path()}\fR\fR  \fIMimeType = string()\fR and \fIExtension = string()\fR. Files delivered to the client are MIME typed according to RFC 1590. File suffixes are mapped to MIME types before file delivery. The mapping between file suffixes and MIME types can be specified in the property list.

.PP
Mime types can also be read from a file. The file should contain lines in the form \fIMediaType [Extensions...]\fR, such as \fItext/html html htm\fR. To configure this, specify the path to it, such as \fI{mime_types, "/etc/mime.types"}\fR.

.PP
If unset, \fIconf/mime.types\fR under \fIserver_root\fR will be used if it exists, otherwise, the default is \fI[{"html","text/html"},{"htm","text/html"}]\fR.

.RE


