\fB\fI{script_re_write, {Re, Replacement}}\fR\fR  \fIRe = string()\fR and \fIReplacement = string()\fR. Have the same behavior as property \fIre_write\fR, except that they also mark the target directory as containing CGI scripts. URLs with a path beginning with url-path are mapped to scripts beginning with directory-filename, for example:

.IP
.nf
{script_re_write, {"^/cgi-bin/(\\\\d+)/", "/web/\\\\1/cgi-bin/"}}

.fi

.PP
Access to http://your.server.org/cgi-bin/17/foo would cause the server to run the script /web/17/cgi-bin/foo.

.RE


