\fB\fI{script_nocache, boolean()}\fR\fR  If \fIscript_nocache\fR is set to \fItrue\fR, the HTTP server by default adds the header fields necessary to prevent proxies from caching the page. Generally this is preferred. Default to \fIfalse\fR.

.RE


